dex and non-thermal luminosity of the source\n(almost the same as those of the Vela pulsar and the recently discovered pulsar\nPSR J 0205+6449 in the supernova remnant 3C 58) suggest that it can be a young\n\"ordinary\" pulsar.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2002 12:50:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Dec 2002 13:31:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
